    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "> Move both tooltips above the slider, so one can still see its value while sliding on a mobile\n\nCareful, you then have to handle tooltip overlaps/find a way for them to not overlap. And ionrangeslider \"merging\" is not so great solution to this.\n\n> Allow one to specify an exact value (maybe directly in the tooltips. We talked about that already)\n\nThis could be an option as proposed by @seafoox and @bobylito where you ask the API to generate `<input/>` to be placed before the slider.\n\n> In other words: we might have to rething the use-cases of where we advocate a slider in a UX perspective\n\nYes slider are fun to develop but a pain to use and design well. A good price range is better in many situations. Or just `<input>`s.\n",
